# Color System Rules for Nine98 App

## Core Principle

**NEVER hardcode colors. Always use semantic classes from `global.css`.**

## Semantic Color Classes (Auto-adapt to light/dark themes)

### Text Colors

- `text-text` - Primary text (gray-900)
- `text-text-secondary` - Secondary/muted text (gray-500)
- `text-text-normal` - Normal text (gray-700)
- `text-text-contrast` - Contrast text (gray-600)
- `text-icon` - Icon color (gray-500)
- `text-tint` - Accent/highlight (primary-500)
- `text-primary` - Brand color (primary-700)

### Background Colors

- `bg-background` - Main background (white)
- `bg-background-gray` - Gray background (gray-50/gray-100)
- `bg-surface` - Card/container background (white)
- `bg-text-contrast` - Contrast background (gray-200)
- `bg-primary` - Brand background (primary-700)

### Border Colors

- `border-border` - Default borders (gray-200)
- `border-primary` - Primary borders (primary-700)

## Status Colors

### Base Status Colors

- Success: `*-success` (#12b76a)
- Error: `*-error` (#f04438)
- Warning: `*-warning` (#f79009)
- Info: `*-info` (primary-500)

### Status Color Scales

Available scales from 10-100 for nuanced designs:

- Success: `*-success-10` through `*-success-100`
- Error: `*-error-10` through `*-error-100`
- Warning: `*-warning-10` through `*-warning-100`

### Light Status Backgrounds (Legacy)

- `bg-success-light` (success-10), `border-success-light` (success-20)
- `bg-error-light` (error-10), `border-error-light` (error-20)
- `bg-warning-light` (warning-10), `border-warning-light` (warning-20)
- `bg-info-light` (primary-100), `border-info-light` (primary-200)

## Color Scales

### Primary Scale

`*-primary-50` through `*-primary-950`

### Gray Scale

`*-gray-50` through `*-gray-900`

## Alternative Colors

