// Error state
<TextInput
  className="bg-surface border border-error rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-text"
/>
```

## Color Violations to Avoid

### ❌ NEVER Use

```tsx
// Hex colors
className="text-[#2d489a]"
style={{ color: '#000000' }}

// RGB/RGBA
style={{ backgroundColor: 'rgb(255, 255, 255)' }}

// Non-semantic Tailwind
className="bg-blue-500 text-gray-700"

// Dark mode prefixes
className="dark:bg-gray-900 dark:text-white"

// Arbitrary values
className="bg-[#f3f4f6]"
```

### ✅ ALWAYS Use

```tsx
// Semantic classes
className = 'bg-background text-text';
className = 'bg-surface border-border';
className = 'text-success bg-success-10';
className = 'bg-primary-100 text-primary-700';
```

## Common Color Mappings

| Instead of        | Use                             |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------- |
| `bg-white`        | `bg-background` or `bg-surface` |
| `bg-gray-50`      | `bg-background-gray`            |
| `text-gray-900`   | `text-text`                     |
| `text-gray-500`   | `text-text-secondary`           |
| `text-gray-700`   | `text-text-normal`              |
| `border-gray-200` | `border-border`                 |
| `bg-blue-600`     | `bg-primary`                    |
| `text-green-600`  | `text-success`                  |
| `text-red-600`    | `text-error`                    |
| `text-yellow-600` | `text-warning`                  |

## Theme Support Rules

1. **Semantic colors auto-adapt** - No manual theme switching needed
2. **Never use `dark:` prefix** - Semantic colors handle it
3. **Trust the system** - CSS custom properties manage themes
4. **Stay semantic** - Use color names that describe purpose, not appearance

## Quick Reference Checklist

1. ✅ Use only semantic color classes from global.css
2. ✅ Let CSS custom properties handle theme switching
3. ✅ Use full color scales (10-100) for nuanced designs
4. ✅ Apply status colors for user feedback
5. ❌ Never hardcode hex/rgb colors
6. ❌ Never use dark: prefixes
7. ❌ Never use non-semantic Tailwind colors

